  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;22:14">Create a new JSON rule set file that markdown-validator can use to
  validate your documentation. Start with a minimal structure and add rules
  incrementally.</shortdesc>

  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="taskbody:1;26:13">

    <prereq id="prereq" class="- topic/section task/prereq " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="prereq:1;28:25">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:1;29:10">markdown-validator is installed. See
      <xref href="../../user-guide/tasks/t_install.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:1;30:58" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Install markdown-validator<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Install markdown-validator with pip in a Python virtual environment.   After installation, the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_install.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;24:35">md-validate</codeph> command is available from   your terminal.</desc></xref>.
      Review the rule set structure before creating your file:
      <xref href="../concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:2;32:58" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Understanding rule sets<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">A rule set is a JSON file that tells markdown-validator what to   check in a Markdown document. It contains two sections: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;25:67">rules</codeph>,   which defines individual checks, and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;26:48">workflows</codeph>, which chains   rules together with conditional logic.</desc></xref>.</p>
    </prereq>

    <context id="context" class="- topic/section task/context " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="context:1;35:27">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:2;36:10">A rule set file is a plain JSON file. Create it in the
      <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="filepath:1;37:17">rules/</filepath> directory of your documentation repository so
      that it is version-controlled alongside the content it governs.</p>
    </context>

    <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="steps:1;41:12">

