          example <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="filepath:2;47:29">rules/tutorial.json</filepath> or
          <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="filepath:3;48:21">rules/reference.json</filepath>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-add-structure" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="step:2;52:37">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="cmd:2;53:14">Add the top-level JSON structure.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="info:2;54:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;55:43">{
  "rules": {
    "header": [],
    "body":   []
  },
  "workflows": []
}</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:4;62:14">This is a valid, empty rule set. No rules means no checks — all
          files will pass until you add rules.</p>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-add-first-rule" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="step:3;67:38">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="cmd:3;68:14">Add your first header rule to check a required front-matter
        field.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="info:3;70:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;71:43">{
  "rules": {
    "header": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "ms-topic-must-exist",
        "type": "header",
        "query": "ms.topic",
        "flag": "check",
        "operation": "==",
        "value": "true",
        "level": "Required",
        "mitigation": "Add ms.topic to the front matter."
      }
    ],
    "body": []
  },
  "workflows": []
}</codeblock>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-validate-structure" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="step:4;93:42">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="cmd:4;94:14">Test the rule set by running it against a sample document.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="info:4;95:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="codeblock:3;96:43">md-validate validate sample.md --rules rules/tutorial.json</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:5;97:14">If the JSON is malformed, the tool reports a schema error.
          Fix the JSON and re-run.</p>
        </info>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="stepresult:1;100:21">The validation report confirms the rule set loads and
