      </step>

    </steps>

    <postreq id="postreq" class="- topic/section task/postreq " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="postreq:1;106:27">
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="ul:1;107:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="li:1;108:13">To add header rules, see
        <xref href="t_write-header-rule.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:3;109:47" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Write a header rule<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Header rules check the YAML front-matter metadata at the top of   your Markdown files. Use them to enforce required fields, expected values,   date freshness, and naming patterns.</desc></xref>.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="li:2;110:13">To add body rules, see
        <xref href="t_write-body-rule.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_create-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:4;111:45" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Write a body rule<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Body rules check the content of your Markdown documents — headings,   sections, paragraph structure, and text patterns. They use XPath expressions   to query the rendered HTML. Test your XPath expressions in the REPL before   adding them to a rule.</desc></xref>.</li>
      </ul>
    </postreq>

